<subSubSection pageId="93" pageNumber="577" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="93.[742,1334,2708,3132]" lastBlockId="93.[127,1331,3136,3486]" pageId="93" pageNumber="577">
<taxonomicName box="[742,950,2862,2895]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="toltecus">Artibeus toltecus</taxonomicName>
1s placed in 
<taxonomicName box="[1141,1289,2862,2895]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Dermanura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Dermanura</taxonomicName>
by some authors but was reassigned to 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Artibeus</taxonomicName>
(subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[972,1120,2940,2973]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Dermanura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Dermanura</taxonomicName>
) according to reinterpretation of molecular results. Some authors included 
<taxonomicName box="[1108,1332,3024,3053]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Dermanura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rava">Dermanura rava</taxonomicName>
as a South American species of A. 
<taxonomicName box="[1235,1325,3059,3092]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="toltecus">toltecus</taxonomicName>
, but it is a distinct species. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
